This paper deals with optimization problems in artificial intelligence, specifically in the area of constraint satisfaction. It discusses techniques for efficiently solving weighted constraint satisfaction problems with high arity cost functions, which are often derived from hard global constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of flow networks to represent global cost functions, which suggests a possible categorization under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper presents empirical results using various benchmarks, indicating a possible categorization under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
